# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# expo-web-dashboard (admin / investor dashboard) — environment example
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in YOUR values.
# `.env.local` is git-ignored. Only VITE_-prefixed vars reach the browser.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Base URL of the NestJS backend API (trailing slash optional — normalized).
# Desktop dev can leave this unset (falls back to http://localhost:3000).
# For LAN testing, use your laptop IPv4 from `ipconfig`:
# VITE_API_URL=http://192.168.1.5:3000

# Default value pre-filled in the "Visitor QR" generator input. Use the
# expo-mobile-app dev-server URL. For a phone-scannable QR, use the laptop
# IPv4 (NOT localhost), e.g.:
# VITE_VISITOR_APP_URL=http://192.168.1.5:5173/
